&lt;p&gt;Hywel Dda Health Board is currently looking for motivated and enthusiastic nurses to join our nursing teams within Acute Services in Pembrokeshire.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Ward One is a Trauma and Orthopaedic ward that specialises in trauma and elective procedures. The ward also specialises in the management of spinal fractures and hip fractures and will provide you with the opportunity to care for patients with complex needs.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants must be committed, possess high levels of drive and initiative, have excellent communication skills, be able to work within a team and maintain high professional care standards. If you are a caring, forward-thinking Registered Nurse who is pro-active and wants to make a valuable contribution to patient focused services, we want to hear from you. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post offer nurses the chance to work in a friendly, supportive environment, where CPD is actively encouraged. You will have the opportunity to develop your skills and experience, whilst making a real difference to patient care. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will need a flexible approach to work to meet the needs of the service, as these posts are rotational - day and night shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
